LogFile.FinalText: Some claim that men and women each speak their different language. If a man - when part of marriage-like situation - says that he does not wish to talk about his problems the state-of-the-art woman will feel that she is let out of his world. If the woman tells him that she does not wish to talk about problems, most men believe that she has no need to talk about them. This misunderstandings often give rise to quarrels. When deep quarrels happen, women and men react differently, too. New research findings show that many women cry when they are angry. In such situations terrified men choose to flee, and they may feel helpless. Contrary to the weeping woman the angry man use harsh words. In spite of different reactions, most men and women succeed in living peacefully together, and anyway we cannot live without each other.
